  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">SET PATH Command</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><snippet src="__CommandInclude" inline="false"/></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Heading1">Purpose</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Change the setting that determines the &lt;%APP%&gt; search path for opening files.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Heading1">Syntax</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">SET PATH TO [&lt;<text styleclass="Italic">xcPathSpecList</text>&gt;]</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Heading1">Description</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">SET PATH is functionally equivalent to SetPath() except that semicolons are not allowed as separators in SET PATH&apos;s &lt;<text styleclass="Italic">xcPathSpecList</text>&gt;. &#160;</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><snippet src="__IncludeLibRT" inline="false"/></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
